Using EC2 for this learning so as to not install cruft on personal laptop

Launch Amazon Linux 2 EC2, t2.nano in public Subnet and public IP

## Install NodeJS ##
curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.34.0/install.sh | bash
. ~/.nvm/nvm.sh
nvm install node

npm --version   - to test install

## Install Python venv ##

yum install python3 pip3
pip3 install virtualenv

## setup AWS access ##
used IAM User and not a Role.

aws configure

## Install CDK ##
npm install -g aws-cdk@latest

cdk --version - to test install is working 

cdk bootstrap aws://<account Id>/<region> - bootstrap account


CDK should in stalled and ready to roll
